would like to drop it from the Windows tlperl installation for the
2019 release. This means that by that time Windows users will no
longer have access to the old GUIs.

Another alternative GUI is tlcockpit, which is based on Java.  And
tlmgr has a `shell' command, for text-mode interactive sessions.  It
is in fact this shell mode that made implementation of a separate
GUI frontend relatively straightforward.

